On International Holocaust Remembrance Day, the President acknowledges the barbaric crime committed against six million Jews and millions of other innocent victims in Nazi death camps. He mourns the lives lost and communities destroyed but also highlights the hope that arises from the liberation of Auschwitz on this day 69 years ago. The President emphasizes the importance of confronting bigotry, especially anti-Semitism, and condemning Holocaust denial. He calls for justice and support for survivors, and reaffirms the obligation to not only bear witness but also to take action. The President and the First Lady stand with the American people, the State of Israel, and the world in remembering the Holocaust and making a solemn vow to never forget and never let such atrocities happen again.